    "By leveraging the cost matrix, the classification of a given example is guided by the minimum expected cost principle (Elkan 2001; López et al. 2013; Fernández et al. 2018; Ling and Sheng 2008).",
    "Accordingly, the example is classified into the class with the lowest expected cost.",
